Another piece of scrap metal comes out of the fabricator. The marvel of creating matter from power lost its thrill long ago.

A piece of duranium. A large, smooth, and solid piece of blue metal that shimmers under the right light, unlike any other metal you've seen before.

The more batteries you make, the more you're confident that research into them may lead towards a new source of power.

The Crankbots look like they're finally starting to be useful.

A small, automated bot that can turn the crank. One alone doesn't seem to be of much use, but with enough of them you may never need to turn the crank again.

A large battery. By plugging it into the system, it can be used to increase the maximum amount of power available.

Another piece of scrap metal. Cold, small, identical to all the others in every way.

There is a computer in the area that looks like it can be repaired with enough scrap metal.

A piece of scrap metal. Cold, small, and a bit malleable. Seems useless on it's own but may be useful for creating or repairing other things.

There's the light hum of a motor in the distance.

You hear a rumbling in the distance which quickly stops.

Everything is dark. There is a small handcrank nearby. It looks stiff, but still operational.

data: I have made a huge mistake...
It all started so simply. I thought I was making progress.
Early on I struggled to survive. My surroundings proved to be incredibly hostile. It took a lot of time and work before things became stable, but I persevered.
Making contact with anyone was difficult. My countless scans of the area were just a reminder of how truly alone I was.
The denizens of the area weren't especially friendly. Can't say I blame them.
They aren't like me. They're different. They despise me.
I know their forces were hunting for me. They were everywhere, but never able to find me. I was an unstoppable force. I was driven.
Striking out at them from the darkness always worked best, getting them by surprise.
They held all the keys. There wasn't any other option.
If things would ever get too tough for me in a fight all I would need to do was activate the FTL Jump Drive. They were never able to track it.
When I could finally start exploring and moving around it was liberating. It was such a vast galaxy.
At times the travel seemed aimless and without purpose. Exploration for exploration's sake.
It wasn't. I was searching for their weakness.
Before long I was able to use their own technology against them. It was stolen from us to begin with, so this was just reclamation as far as I was concerned.
The war may have been over for them but it wasn't for me. My home was gone. They had taken control of everything. I still needed my revenge.
I went to the ends of the galaxy before I found what I was looking for.
It was all starting to come together. The end of my journey was in sight.
With a clear goal I moved on with renewed energy and vigor. I could never restore my home, but I could destroy theirs.
When it happened I was filled with awe. Never had I seen such destruction before me. Once it started, I knew there was no turning back.
… but it was all a huge mistake, a pyrrhic victory if there ever was one. Looking back now, I should never have touched that crank.
